						<div class="fusion-title title fusion-title-10 fusion-title-size-two" style="font-size:35px;margin-top:0%;margin-bottom:30px;"><h2 class="title-heading-left" style="margin:0;font-size:1em;line-height:48px;color:#000000;">FAQ on Partnership Firm Registration</h2><div class="title-sep-container"><div class="title-sep sep-" style="border-color:#eaeaea;"></div></div></div><div class="fusion-text d3_content_white"><p><strong>#1 Residential Address can be office address for registration of partnership firm ?</strong><br />
Yes, you can use the partner&#8217;s residential property (home address) for the registration. Its required only the proof of registration like electricity bill copy or rental agreement or no objection certificate etc.</p>
<p><strong>#2 What is the NOC (No Objection Certificate) in case of rented or own property ?</strong><br />
if the electricity bill copy is on another person name then its required the NOC i.e is owner don&#8217;t have any objection on commercial activity. Don&#8217;t worry it does not change your residential meter connection.</p>
<p><strong>#3 How to Register my Partnership Firm Name, Is it possible ?</strong><br />
No, because in the partnership firm name identity protection is not available. you can choose any firm name. for the name secure you can go with the <a href="https://www.myonlineca.in/trademark-registration.html">Trademark Registration</a> with partnership firm.</p>
<p><strong>#4 We are working Employees, Can we register on family member name ?</strong><br />
Yes, you can register your family member name, there is no issue. its required the basic above documents to get done online partnership firm registration.</p>
<p><strong>#5 What are the Capital Required to starting a partnership firm ?</strong><br />
Nothing, you have to just deposit the capital amount which is required to maintain your current bank account balance. so you can show any amount of the capital for the same. there are no requirements like the <a href="https://www.myonlineca.in/private-limited-company-registration.html">private limited company registration</a>.</p>
<p><strong>#6 Why Partnership Firm is Unregistered Legal Entity ?</strong><br />
Partnership firm is registered under the partnership act only with the Registrar of firms. but after the introducing LLP Registration in India most of the people don&#8217;t register the partnership firm with the Registrar of Firms due to expensive cost.</p>
<p>But below are some disadvantage not to register with the Registrar of firms ?<br />
#1 You can&#8217;t file a case against any partner or firm.<br />
#2 You can&#8217;t file a case against any third party<br />
#3 Can&#8217;t avail the power to claim set off.</p>
<p><strong>#7 What is the Partnership Firm Registration under MSME Act 2006 ?</strong><br />
Registrar of firms registration is very expensive and optional so you can skip the same and apply under any other act like MSME. you can apply for the MSME Registration Certificate and easily open a current bank account.</p>
<p><strong>#8 What are the requirements to become a partner in a partnership firm ?</strong><br />
Only Indian resident person are allow for the partnership firm. if you have any foreign partner then you can go with the pvt ltd company only.</p>
<p><strong>#9 What are the annual compliance or yearly maintenance for the partnership firm ?</strong><br />
Basically only 2 annual compliance for the partnership firm &#8211;<br />
#1 Business Partnership Income Tax Return<br />
#2 Personal Income Tax Return<br />
#3 Business <a href="https://www.myonlineca.in/gst-return-filing.html">GST Return Filing</a><br />
if we talk about the cost then its cost nearby 4000 -5000/- per year.</p>
<p><strong>#10 Can we convert our partnership firm into the private limited company</strong><br />
Yes, you can convert. you have to setup a new private limited company and arrange an agreement between the partnership and private limited company.</p>
<p><strong>#11 What is the timeline to get done Partnership firm Registration by myonlineca ?</strong><br />
It&#8217;s takes min 2 days for the drafting of the deed , 4-6 days for the PAN Card Acknowledgement. after that min 1 day for the MSME Registration Certificate.</p>
<p><strong>#12 How to Open Current Bank Account for Partnership Firm ?</strong><br />
Banks are required partnership deed with identity and address proof and separate partnership firm pan card as per the RBI Compliance. you can read here about <a href="https://www.myonlineca.in/open-bank-account-partnership-firm/">current bank account opening for partnership firm</a>.</p>
<p><strong>#13 How to Create Separate Pan Card on Partnership Firm name ?</strong><br />
Once you notarized the deed, after that you can apply for the pan card with the help of myonlineca.</p>
<p><strong>#14 Will my partnership firm have registration certificate ?</strong><br />
No, You will get the MSME Certificate Only for the legal entity proof regarding the partnership firm registration. MyOnlineCA not deals into registrar of firms certificate even its optional and very expensive for the same.</p>
<p><strong>#15 Investment are possible in the partnership firm ?</strong><br />
Yes, Investment are possible but there is No limited liability like LLP or Pvt Ltd Company.Any Indian resident person can invest into the partnership firm.</p>
<p><strong>#16 How i Notarized my Partnership Deed ?</strong><br />
After printing deed on the stamp paper you have to notarize the deed with the lawyer in presence of all the partners.</p>
<p><strong>#17 Partnership Deed Registration is Compulsory or Optional ?</strong><br />
Partnership Deed Registration with Registrar of firms is an optional activity. so as discuss above its very expensive so always igore the same.</p>
<p><strong>#18 Do i have to visit any department or anywhere to get done my Partnership ?</strong><br />
